ndgain-id_food_03-score.def:
Description: Proportion of cereal consumption obtained from imports. The definition of cereal is from FAO referred as “crops harvested for dry grain only”, including wheat, rice, barley, maize, popcorn, rye, oats, millets, sorghum, buckwheat, quinoa, fonio, triticale, canary seed, mixed grain, and remaining types (FAO, n.d.). Cereal consumption is equal to production and imports minus exports. 
Rationale: Countries highly dependent on food imports are susceptible to shocks in food prices in the international market. Climate change and its impacts on the agriculture sector may accentuate price volatility (Nelson et al., 2010).
ndgain-id_food_03-score.name: Food import dependency
